Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; exterior: remnants of dark grey slip; remains of inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: There is a modern incised inscription on inside 'Diosk' indicates findspot. The sherd joins British Museum 1888,0601.618 and also belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1965,0930.428. The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.150)
